cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.CC

This paper deals with nonmonotonic reasoning in Description Logics, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on circumscription, which is a technique used in logic and knowledge representation, falling under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of reasoning in DLs, which is related to Database Theory (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper involves language restrictions and constraints, which are relevant to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
